it seems to be connecting to an eero node in my network that is far from being the strongest signal. how do i make it reconnect to the one with the strongest signal. seems it should be automatic.
While mesh systems like eero are designed to handle this automatically through "Client Steering," the decision to switch (roam) is ultimately made by your device's WiFi driver. Linux often "clings" to a weak signal because the threshold to trigger a new search hasn't been met. 
1. Manual Reconnect to the Best Node 
To force an immediate reconnection to the strongest available eero node, you can trigger a rescan and then tell nmcli to connect to the specific BSSID (MAC address) of the node with the best signal. 
Find the BSSID of the strongest node:
bash
nmcli -f IN-USE,BSSID,SIGNAL,SSID device wifi list | grep "Your_SSID_Name"
Use code with caution.

Connect directly to that BSSID:
Identify the BSSID (e.g., AA:BB:CC:11:22:33) with the highest signal percentage and run:
bash
nmcli device wifi connect AA:BB:CC:11:22:33
Use code with caution.

 
2. Force a Fresh Scan & Auto-Selection
If you don't want to specify a BSSID, you can force the system to drop the current weak connection and re-evaluate all nodes. It will typically pick the strongest one during the handshake. 
bash
nmcli device wifi rescan && nmcli device wifi connect "Your_SSID_Name"
Use code with caution.

3. Improving Automatic "Roaming"
To make this process more automatic in the future, check these settings:
Enable Client Steering: In the eero app, ensure "Client Steering" (found under Settings > Network Settings) is turned ON. This allows eero to actively encourage your device to move to a better node.
Toggle WiFi: Often, simply cycling the interface is enough to trigger a roam to the nearest node:
bash
nmcli radio wifi off && nmcli radio wifi on
Use code with caution.

BSSID Locking (Caution): You can technically "lock" your device to a specific eero node by setting the 802-11-wireless.bssid property in your connection profile. However, this is generally discouraged for laptops, as you will lose connectivity entirely when you move to another room. 
Summary of Commands
Action 	Command
List Strengths	nmcli -f BSSID,SIGNAL,SSID device wifi list
Force Best Node	nmcli device wifi connect <BSSID_OF_STRONGEST>
Quick Reset	nmcli radio wifi off && nmcli radio wifi on




